target_title: cinnamon-control-center compatibility issue
Blank VPN tab when creating or editing connection in nm-connection-editor

note.body:
I see the following with network-manager-vpnc 1.4.0 and `nm-connection-editor` on Debian Sid:

`** (nm-connection-editor:2881): WARNING **: 11:28:11.535: Could not load editor VPN plugin for “org.freedesktop.NetworkManager.vpnc” (cannot load factory nm_vpn_editor_factory_vpnc from plugin: /usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/NetworkManager/libnm-vpn-plugin-vpnc-editor.so: undefined symbol: nm_vpn_editor_factory_vpnc).`


The `undefined symbol: nm_vpn_editor_factory_vpnc` error seems to be a result of commit https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/NetworkManager-vpnc/-/commit/e2fc231149165cb37a25362b85cbcd58b15a2a11 unintentionally removing the `nm_vpn_editor_factory_vpnc()` function from `properties/nm-vpnc-editor.c`.

note.body: Also experiencing this issue - downgrading to 1.2.8 worked.

target_title: 1.2.8: autoconf executed with --with-gtk4 fails because missing gtk+-3.0

note.body:
For now gtk-3.0 is needed because the auth dialog depends on gtk-3.0 and for the time being I'm not being convinced porting to gtk-4.0 is going to help with anything because gtk-3.0 is just more likely to be available.

Is there any particular reason you'd want to avoid gtk-3.0?
